tweet: Josh knows we need an AG that is independent and a watchdog for Wisconsinites. If #Foxconn tries to come back to the table and renegotiate for better terms, we need an AG that we can count on to stand up for us. #WiAGdebate #wipolitics

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: .@BradSchimel wants to go back to the old system when insurance companies could discriminate against people with pre-existing conditions. Make no mistake: that's what his lawsuit does.

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: Under our prior AG – a Republican – we collected over $3 million a year in fines from polluters. That’s dropped to less than $1 million under @BradSchimel's leadership. When polluters break the law, Josh knows they should be held accountable.

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: .@BradSchimel makes excuses for his failure to test the backlogged rape kits despite getting millions of dollars to address the backlog in his first year in office. Only 9 of the over 4,000 kits were tested in his first two years in office.

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: .@BradSchimel repeats his support for putting guns in schools. Josh will fight against any effort to arm teachers.

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: We need an AG that will stand up for Wisconsin and won't take contributions from pharmaceutical companies, unlike @BradSchimel #WiAGdebate #wipolitics

name: Josh Kaul
tweet: We need an AG who is going to hold the pharmaceutical companies accountable for the role they have played in creating and exacerbating this epidemic.  And Josh knows we need to expand Medicaid so more Wisconsinites have access to treatment. #wipolitics #WiAGdebate

tweet: Wisconsin had almost 900 opioid related overdose deaths last year. Josh knows we must start treating the opioid epidemic like the crisis it is. We should be focusing our enforcement efforts on large-scale drug traffickers and expanding access to treatment. #wipolitics #WiAGdebate
